        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down.</hi> | Beckenham | <hi rend="print">Kent. S.E.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>Nov 18.</date>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I beg leave to thank you for the honour which you have done me in sending me your fine Memoir on the Bacillariæ of Mexico.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> With my best thanks &amp; the most sincere respect</p>
<p>I beg leave to remain | yours truly obliged | Charles Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 Beckenham] <hi rend="italic">before del</hi> ‘<hi rend="italic">Bromley.</hi>’ </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The year is established by the publication date of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2287.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ehrenberg 1869</ref> (see n. 2, below).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The reference is to <hi rend="italic">Uber mächtige Gebirgs-Schichten vorherrschend aus mikroskopischen Bacillarien unter und bei der Stadt Mexiko</hi> (<ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2287.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Ehrenberg 1869</ref>).</note>
